      <hedline>
        <hl1>In 50 States</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>William Closs letter on W D Wetherell's June 4 travel article notes he achieved his 50th state visit several years ago with trip to Arkansas; suggests train trip to Pacific Northwest (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I achieved my 50th state several years ago with a special journey to Arkansas.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: I achieved my 50th state several years ago with a special journey to Arkansas.</p>
        <p>On the important question as to whether an airport visit counts, I suggest it shouldn't. Try riding the train. I bagged the elusive North Dakota (and several others) on an Amtrak trip to the Pacific Northwest. Train travel permits one to experience a place. There is a stop for a walk-around every four to five hours. In North Dakota, the train stops in Minot for 40 minutes.</p>
        <p>WILLIAM CLOSS  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
